1
00:00:08,008 --> 00:00:09,243
Good morning!

2
00:00:13,947 --> 00:00:14,748
What...?

3
00:00:32,232 --> 00:00:35,035
Fashion Expert Partner?

4
00:00:35,335 --> 00:00:36,203
What's that?

5
00:00:36,236 --> 00:00:37,871
It doesn't matter.

6
00:00:37,905 --> 00:00:40,140
She's well and thriving.

7
00:00:41,308 --> 00:00:42,676
Ta-da.

8
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:46,546
I bet you'd look good in this.

9
00:00:47,014 --> 00:00:48,515
Pretty sophisticated, huh?

10
00:00:51,385 --> 00:00:53,921
We sold 50 thousand copies in Paris!

11
00:00:58,325 --> 00:00:59,626
Mr. Arazome!

12
00:01:29,890 --> 00:01:35,829
Global Fashion Expert Partner
Nami Suzuki

13
00:01:43,270 --> 00:01:46,840
So much has happened
to get where I am now.

14
00:01:47,741 --> 00:01:50,043
Coming to Tokyo knowing nothing.

15
00:01:50,077 --> 00:01:52,212
Pushed around by a tough boss.

16
00:01:52,245 --> 00:01:55,082
But somehow managing
to publish the first issue.

17
00:01:55,716 --> 00:01:58,552
They looked so awesome then.

18
00:01:59,119 --> 00:02:01,188
I met a puppy-like boy too.

19
00:02:02,222 --> 00:02:03,523
That's right.

20
00:02:03,557 --> 00:02:07,594
I went to his exhibition,
and he kissed me on my forehead.

21
00:02:08,962 --> 00:02:10,464
Kissed me on my forehead?

22
00:02:10,697 --> 00:02:13,400
I ran home after that happened.

23
00:02:14,101 --> 00:02:15,936
But what was that about?

24
00:02:19,606 --> 00:02:24,277
It's definitely different
from his past suggestive behavior.

25
00:02:24,778 --> 00:02:27,080
He's clearly telling me something.

26
00:02:28,949 --> 00:02:30,050
You think he likes me?

27
00:02:30,784 --> 00:02:31,985
Impossible.

28
00:02:32,019 --> 00:02:34,254
He said I wasn't someone he'd date.

29
00:02:35,055 --> 00:02:39,126
Are kisses on the forehead
normal for Tokyo people?

30
00:02:42,462 --> 00:02:43,797
So cute.

31
00:02:48,268 --> 00:02:51,171
That cute little puppy
is leading me on.

32
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:54,474
Stop it.

33
00:02:55,008 --> 00:02:58,078
Stop whining like that.
You'll make me fall for you.

34
00:02:58,412 --> 00:03:02,082
Like the saying goes,
"Beat the bridge before you cross it."

35
00:03:02,115 --> 00:03:03,483
No, I can't cross it.

36
00:03:03,717 --> 00:03:05,752
I have to beat it over and over.

37
00:03:05,919 --> 00:03:08,822
Until it's broken!

38
00:03:08,855 --> 00:03:12,826
Stop leading me on!

39
00:03:21,668 --> 00:03:23,103
Tami

40
00:03:23,136 --> 00:03:25,405
We saw Miyavi.

41
00:03:28,275 --> 00:03:29,743
Oh, hey guys.

42
00:03:29,776 --> 00:03:34,014
- Fashion...
- Expert Partner!

43
00:03:34,347 --> 00:03:36,450
Stop it, you're embarrassing me.

44
00:03:36,483 --> 00:03:38,185
You're famous now.

45
00:03:38,418 --> 00:03:42,556
Mr. Uehara, your teacher
from junior high even called.

46
00:03:42,589 --> 00:03:45,358
Tama Sushi even sent dinner over.

47
00:03:45,392 --> 00:03:46,760
Jeez.

48
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:48,695
It's not that big a deal.

49
00:03:48,728 --> 00:03:52,032
You're making a fashion magazine
in Tokyo.

50
00:03:52,065 --> 00:03:54,868
It's nothing really.

51
00:03:56,136 --> 00:04:01,808
Just dining at expensive restaurants
with people in the industry.

52
00:04:02,209 --> 00:04:03,210
Ms. Horai, anyway.

53
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:05,712
And being sent the latest brand bags.

54
00:04:06,046 --> 00:04:06,980
Ms. Horai, anyway.

55
00:04:07,247 --> 00:04:08,348
That's about it.

56
00:04:08,582 --> 00:04:10,183
That's so awesome!

57
00:04:10,584 --> 00:04:11,918
Ms. Horai is, anyway.

58
00:04:11,952 --> 00:04:12,886
I'm Horai.

59
00:04:12,919 --> 00:04:14,321
I'm hanging up.

60
00:04:24,264 --> 00:04:29,336
Since I work for
the latest fashion magazine...

61
00:04:39,546 --> 00:04:40,680
Good morning.

62
00:04:40,714 --> 00:04:41,581
Morning.

63
00:04:43,350 --> 00:04:45,552
Hold up.

64
00:04:45,785 --> 00:04:47,687
What's going on?

65
00:04:48,722 --> 00:04:49,489
Yes?

66
00:04:49,523 --> 00:04:50,891
No, totally no.

67
00:04:50,924 --> 00:04:53,593
What are you wearing?

68
00:04:53,627 --> 00:04:54,795
Some kind of joke?

69
00:04:55,862 --> 00:04:59,232
I hear Miyavi is selling well.

70
00:05:01,835 --> 00:05:06,540
200 thousand copies sold
in this digital era.

71
00:05:07,874 --> 00:05:09,109
That's quite incredible.

72
00:05:10,510 --> 00:05:11,745
Thank you.

73
00:05:12,412 --> 00:05:15,081
But the goal is to sell 300 thousand.

74
00:05:15,115 --> 00:05:15,882
True.

75
00:05:16,416 --> 00:05:18,752
To keep Otowado on its feet,

76
00:05:18,785 --> 00:05:23,290
I'm sorry to say
that this isn't quite enough yet.

77
00:05:23,857 --> 00:05:26,793
But you still have six more months.

78
00:05:32,199 --> 00:05:36,102
I'm thinking of asking her
to be in our next feature.

79
00:05:36,469 --> 00:05:38,672
I would like your permission.

80
00:05:39,439 --> 00:05:43,276
We need her
to overcome this situation.

81
00:05:46,213 --> 00:05:47,547
I don't see why not.

82
00:05:48,782 --> 00:05:50,684
I leave everything up to you.

83
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:54,888
And...

84
00:05:56,890 --> 00:05:59,626
I'm sorry for making you bear
such a heavy load.

85
00:06:00,994 --> 00:06:02,395
I'll do everything I can

86
00:06:02,996 --> 00:06:04,664
to prevent the merger.

87
00:06:06,266 --> 00:06:08,235
How is Reiko doing?

88
00:06:08,501 --> 00:06:11,771
Like always. She probably won't be
visiting home for a while.

89
00:06:11,805 --> 00:06:12,572
Really.

90
00:06:13,673 --> 00:06:16,676
Maybe she would for your wedding.

91
00:06:16,710 --> 00:06:18,545
Come on, stop it.

92
00:06:20,080 --> 00:06:20,880
I'm going.

93
00:06:23,450 --> 00:06:26,086
What about your hamburger steak?

94
00:06:26,119 --> 00:06:27,988
- No thanks.
- And shrimp fries.

95
00:06:36,463 --> 00:06:39,032
Dad and Sis are both grown-ups.

96
00:06:39,766 --> 00:06:41,701
They should just talk it over.

97
00:06:43,036 --> 00:06:44,237
Oh yes, I remembered.

98
00:06:44,571 --> 00:06:46,339
Rio is coming back to Japan.

99
00:06:51,177 --> 00:06:52,679
Is it that bad?

100
00:06:53,280 --> 00:06:55,749
I'm a part of the Miyavi team.

101
00:06:55,782 --> 00:06:58,184
I thought I should be
a bit more fashionable.

102
00:06:58,218 --> 00:06:59,352
It's happening.

103
00:07:00,420 --> 00:07:01,354
It sure is.

104
00:07:01,554 --> 00:07:02,522
What is?

105
00:07:02,555 --> 00:07:03,823
Assistant editor syndrome.

106
00:07:04,991 --> 00:07:06,960
It happens to everyone.

107
00:07:06,993 --> 00:07:09,929
They join the team,
uninterested in fashion.

108
00:07:09,963 --> 00:07:13,400
But they suddenly start
trying to be trendy.

109
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:16,269
You might be right.

110
00:07:16,903 --> 00:07:20,707
You guys were so cool the other day
before the deadline.

111
00:07:20,740 --> 00:07:23,810
I realized I was working
with an incredible team.

112
00:07:23,843 --> 00:07:26,346
So I wanted to be like you guys.

113
00:07:27,213 --> 00:07:29,749
How do I become more fashionable?

114
00:07:31,551 --> 00:07:33,853
What good would that do
to a dirt ball?

115
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:35,822
It'd be a waste.

116
00:07:35,855 --> 00:07:38,625
I want to do some fashion work too.

117
00:07:38,658 --> 00:07:40,860
You'll put this firm out of business.

118
00:07:40,894 --> 00:07:42,329
Am I that bad?

119
00:07:42,362 --> 00:07:45,765
Did you deliver the sweets
to Dolly Harris?

120
00:07:45,799 --> 00:07:47,867
Yes, Otakaya's sweet potato bar.

121
00:07:48,601 --> 00:07:49,636
Sweet potato bar?

122
00:07:52,105 --> 00:07:55,141
I told you to buy a cheese terrine
from Remy Tokyo.

123
00:07:55,175 --> 00:07:58,712
Yes, but Otakaya's sweet potato bars
are sweet but not too...

124
00:07:58,745 --> 00:08:00,714
I'm not asking.

125
00:08:02,649 --> 00:08:04,517
I'll go buy a cheese terrine.

126
00:08:04,551 --> 00:08:05,685
You do that.

127
00:08:10,724 --> 00:08:16,029
I feel sorry for you, worrying about
sweet potato bars and cheese terrines.

128
00:08:16,062 --> 00:08:17,530
That's all I get to do.

129
00:08:17,764 --> 00:08:20,567
I want to do editing work
like you guys.

130
00:08:21,468 --> 00:08:26,639
Do you want to go to Jimmy Choo's
reception party with us?

131
00:08:27,340 --> 00:08:28,608
What's that?

132
00:08:28,641 --> 00:08:33,012
Brands invite clients
and media outlets

133
00:08:33,046 --> 00:08:35,715
to present their new collection.

134
00:08:35,982 --> 00:08:37,283
I'd love to go.

135
00:08:38,318 --> 00:08:39,819
Please take me with you!

136
00:08:43,957 --> 00:08:48,027
Oh My Boss! Love Not Included

137
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:04,210
Are all these people
celebrities and fashion people?

138
00:09:04,244 --> 00:09:05,712
Stop goggling.

139
00:09:05,745 --> 00:09:06,780
- Sorry.
- Look here.

140
00:09:06,813 --> 00:09:09,249
Be sure you greet people properly.

141
00:09:09,516 --> 00:09:10,784
Loud and smart.

142
00:09:12,752 --> 00:09:13,620
Let's go.

143
00:09:16,823 --> 00:09:17,824
Nami?

144
00:09:18,324 --> 00:09:19,626
Hello!

145
00:09:21,861 --> 00:09:22,662
Kenchan?

146
00:09:23,763 --> 00:09:24,864
Kenchan?

147
00:09:26,833 --> 00:09:28,535
A friend from back home.

148
00:09:28,635 --> 00:09:29,402
Hello.

149
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:32,105
We'll see you upstairs.

150
00:09:33,373 --> 00:09:34,941
What are you doing here?

151
00:09:36,209 --> 00:09:39,012
I'm the executives' accountant.

152
00:09:39,045 --> 00:09:40,413
So I was invited.

153
00:09:41,681 --> 00:09:42,782
Oh yeah.

154
00:09:43,016 --> 00:09:45,418
You do editing
for a fashion magazine, right?

155
00:09:45,452 --> 00:09:46,820
Yeah, kind of.

156
00:09:48,788 --> 00:09:52,091
You look pretty fine
dressed up like that.

157
00:09:53,693 --> 00:09:54,461
You look cute.

158
00:09:55,829 --> 00:09:56,930
You think?

159
00:09:57,797 --> 00:10:00,567
I borrowed it all.

160
00:10:03,169 --> 00:10:05,905
If it's okay with you,
it's okay with me.

161
00:10:09,075 --> 00:10:10,176
Want to go out?

162
00:10:10,910 --> 00:10:12,679
- Huh?
- Why not?

163
00:10:12,712 --> 00:10:15,248
What are you talking about?
You're engaged.

164
00:10:15,582 --> 00:10:16,516
Don't worry.

165
00:10:17,050 --> 00:10:17,951
Don't worry?

166
00:10:18,218 --> 00:10:20,253
We can keep it a secret.

167
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:22,455
Let's ditch this party.

168
00:10:23,123 --> 00:10:25,725
Does he mean, like an affair?

169
00:10:27,861 --> 00:10:30,396
Hey stop, I...

170
00:10:40,940 --> 00:10:42,642
What is it?

171
00:10:43,443 --> 00:10:44,878
She told you to stop.

172
00:10:45,545 --> 00:10:46,813
We're old friends.

173
00:10:46,846 --> 00:10:48,114
And I'm her boyfriend.

174
00:10:49,616 --> 00:10:50,984
Boyfriend?

175
00:10:51,217 --> 00:10:54,654
She's my number one,
not your number two.

176
00:10:56,689 --> 00:10:57,757
Let's go.

177
00:10:59,325 --> 00:11:00,527
But...

178
00:11:03,029 --> 00:11:04,764
What's going on?

179
00:11:05,565 --> 00:11:07,300
How am I supposed to feel about this?

180
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:11,204
I want to beat the bridge,
but how can I now?

181
00:11:11,838 --> 00:11:13,740
I don't even have the chance to.

182
00:11:13,773 --> 00:11:15,708
I can't cross this bridge!

183
00:11:23,950 --> 00:11:25,051
Surprised?

184
00:11:26,719 --> 00:11:29,255
I came here on the job and saw you.

185
00:11:30,823 --> 00:11:31,925
So that's Kenchan?

186
00:11:37,764 --> 00:11:38,665
Um.

187
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:42,502
You just said you were my boyfriend.

188
00:11:45,238 --> 00:11:48,441
I got mad because
he treated you like that.

189
00:11:50,209 --> 00:11:51,578
You kissed my forehead.

190
00:11:52,178 --> 00:11:53,079
That kiss?

191
00:11:56,816 --> 00:11:58,017
Yeah.

192
00:12:03,056 --> 00:12:05,692
Because I...

193
00:12:05,725 --> 00:12:06,492
Stand back!

194
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:09,796
If you get any closer,
the bridge will...

195
00:12:10,630 --> 00:12:11,464
Bridge?

196
00:12:11,497 --> 00:12:14,500
Keep a one-meter radius away from me.

197
00:12:15,702 --> 00:12:17,437
So, a two-meter diameter?

198
00:12:17,470 --> 00:12:18,538
Right.

199
00:12:19,739 --> 00:12:20,573
Distance!

200
00:12:32,919 --> 00:12:33,953
Another please.

201
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:35,388
She's here.

202
00:12:40,727 --> 00:12:42,695
Thank you for coming, Ms. Jinko.

203
00:12:42,829 --> 00:12:44,464
It's such an honor.

204
00:12:44,731 --> 00:12:46,733
I was just back in Japan.

205
00:12:46,766 --> 00:12:48,101
I see.

206
00:12:48,134 --> 00:12:49,068
Who?

207
00:12:51,004 --> 00:12:54,273
You work in the industry
and don't know Jinko Uekusa?

208
00:12:54,307 --> 00:12:55,541
You must be bogus.

209
00:12:55,708 --> 00:12:57,443
Editor-in-chief of Deal.

210
00:12:57,477 --> 00:12:58,911
- It's Zeal.
- Zeal.

211
00:12:59,646 --> 00:13:03,049
She started the global kimono trend.

212
00:13:03,449 --> 00:13:05,218
A fashion creative director.

213
00:13:06,853 --> 00:13:09,389
Aren't you going to go
butter up to her?

214
00:13:09,422 --> 00:13:11,224
I know where I stand.

215
00:13:11,524 --> 00:13:14,594
She spread "Japanese mode"
to the world,

216
00:13:14,627 --> 00:13:16,763
the true don of the fashion circle.

217
00:13:16,796 --> 00:13:21,000
If you get her mad,
you'll perish in this industry.

218
00:13:21,567 --> 00:13:24,137
Wake not a sleeping lion.

219
00:13:25,271 --> 00:13:27,173
Oh, Reiko!

220
00:13:28,441 --> 00:13:30,143
Long time no see, Ms. Jinko.

221
00:13:30,343 --> 00:13:32,545
- Ms. Horai?
- When did we meet last?

222
00:13:32,578 --> 00:13:35,081
Before I was editor-in-chief in Paris?

223
00:13:35,114 --> 00:13:36,315
Yes, six years now.

224
00:13:36,349 --> 00:13:38,351
I hear you're doing well.

225
00:13:39,585 --> 00:13:43,923
All thanks to what I learned from you
when I started out.

226
00:13:44,590 --> 00:13:47,794
I can't wait to work with you
for our next feature.

227
00:13:50,797 --> 00:13:53,499
You can't say that, Ms. Horai!

228
00:13:53,533 --> 00:13:56,235
It hasn't been published yet,
that's a spoiler!

229
00:13:56,269 --> 00:13:58,971
No, it's for the publicity.

230
00:13:59,005 --> 00:14:00,940
Please don't post that.

231
00:14:00,973 --> 00:14:03,743
I see you have
a spunky little assistant.

232
00:14:03,776 --> 00:14:07,180
It's a secret, okay?

233
00:14:07,213 --> 00:14:08,381
Suzuki.

234
00:14:11,784 --> 00:14:12,752
Why?

235
00:14:21,427 --> 00:14:23,396
Jinko Uekusa

236
00:14:25,932 --> 00:14:27,166
Hello.

237
00:14:27,433 --> 00:14:28,367
This way please.

238
00:14:28,401 --> 00:14:29,635
Thank you.

239
00:14:30,136 --> 00:14:32,405
A visitor
from Miyavi's editing department.

240
00:14:35,408 --> 00:14:36,375
One moment.

241
00:14:36,776 --> 00:14:37,543
Excuse me.

242
00:14:37,577 --> 00:14:42,348
I want to go with a completely
different concept from last month's.

243
00:14:42,381 --> 00:14:44,250
Really gorgeous and all out.

244
00:14:44,650 --> 00:14:45,918
What do you think, Marika?

245
00:14:46,018 --> 00:14:47,019
Sounds perfect.

246
00:14:48,187 --> 00:14:49,088
Right?

247
00:14:49,889 --> 00:14:53,025
How about you three?
I want your honest opinion.

248
00:14:53,493 --> 00:14:54,794
I agree too.

249
00:14:54,827 --> 00:14:55,895
Me too.

250
00:14:55,928 --> 00:14:56,996
I knew it.

251
00:14:57,997 --> 00:15:01,734
I'm thinking of using
some Harry Winston pieces.

252
00:15:01,768 --> 00:15:02,802
Is that too much?

253
00:15:03,102 --> 00:15:05,104
No, it would be perfect.

254
00:15:05,505 --> 00:15:06,272
Yes.

255
00:15:08,508 --> 00:15:11,010
Something like the Hope Diamond.

256
00:15:15,047 --> 00:15:16,015
I'm here.

257
00:15:17,483 --> 00:15:19,118
Sorry for bothering you.

258
00:15:19,385 --> 00:15:22,989
Here are some sweets
from our editor-in-chief.

259
00:15:23,022 --> 00:15:26,659
From Reiko? She shouldn't have.

260
00:15:26,692 --> 00:15:30,963
Everyone, Miyavi's editor-in-chief
has sent us some sweets.

261
00:15:31,264 --> 00:15:32,765
Thank you.

262
00:15:34,534 --> 00:15:35,768
Tell Reiko I said hi.

263
00:15:36,068 --> 00:15:38,037
I will. Thank you.

264
00:15:39,138 --> 00:15:40,006
I'll go now.

265
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:41,774
Goodbye.

266
00:15:44,477 --> 00:15:45,444
One second.

267
00:15:48,581 --> 00:15:50,783
I'm going to Omotesando.

268
00:15:51,217 --> 00:15:53,019
Won't you show me around?

269
00:15:54,520 --> 00:15:56,556
I shall drive.

270
00:15:56,589 --> 00:15:57,957
It's fine, I'll take a cab.

271
00:15:58,391 --> 00:15:59,826
Take a little break.

272
00:16:01,427 --> 00:16:03,362
What a nice team.

273
00:16:03,396 --> 00:16:05,131
So friendly.

274
00:16:05,865 --> 00:16:08,401
I try to encourage open conversation.

275
00:16:08,768 --> 00:16:13,673
Work efficiency will drop if they feel
uncomfortable, don't you think?

276
00:16:13,706 --> 00:16:14,674
Yes.

277
00:16:15,675 --> 00:16:18,110
I wish my boss were more like you.

278
00:16:19,011 --> 00:16:23,382
I don't want to say this,
but she's a real devil.

279
00:16:23,683 --> 00:16:27,019
I tried to be fashionable,
but she called me a dirt ball.

280
00:16:28,754 --> 00:16:30,056
How cruel.

281
00:16:30,756 --> 00:16:34,026
You've known Ms. Horai
for years, right?

282
00:16:34,060 --> 00:16:38,130
Did she make any stupid mistakes
when she was a newbie?

283
00:16:38,397 --> 00:16:39,732
I don't recall any.

284
00:16:40,199 --> 00:16:41,801
I'll tell you if I do.

285
00:16:43,169 --> 00:16:47,573
By the way, your company's
vice president is Mr. Ugaji, right?

286
00:16:47,607 --> 00:16:49,609
I'd like to dine with him.

287
00:16:49,976 --> 00:16:51,377
You know him?

288
00:16:51,611 --> 00:16:53,112
He's an old acquaintance.

289
00:16:53,613 --> 00:16:56,949
We divorced 15 years ago.

290
00:16:56,983 --> 00:16:58,784
15 years.

291
00:17:00,119 --> 00:17:01,020
Huh, divorced?

292
00:17:01,387 --> 00:17:02,421
You were married to him?

293
00:17:04,323 --> 00:17:05,858
I'm sorry.

294
00:17:07,593 --> 00:17:11,130
That's fine. I can't ask my staff
such a personal favor.

295
00:17:11,364 --> 00:17:12,899
That's why you're asking me.

296
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:15,701
Okay, no problem.

297
00:17:16,369 --> 00:17:17,670
Thank you.

298
00:17:19,138 --> 00:17:21,073
By the way,

299
00:17:21,107 --> 00:17:24,610
would you like to help me
with this feature?

300
00:17:25,211 --> 00:17:27,580
Can I? I'd love to!

301
00:17:28,214 --> 00:17:29,515
So you're quitting.

302
00:17:29,548 --> 00:17:30,683
Nice knowing you.

303
00:17:31,050 --> 00:17:34,754
You're going to miss me when I'm gone.

304
00:17:34,787 --> 00:17:36,222
Nami!

305
00:17:36,255 --> 00:17:37,490
Why?

306
00:17:37,523 --> 00:17:39,525
Let's go see the stars.

307
00:17:39,792 --> 00:17:42,595
I can trust him, right?

308
00:17:52,305 --> 00:17:55,541
Mr. Ugaji! I, um...

309
00:17:55,575 --> 00:17:58,544
I have a message for you
from Ms. Jinko Uekusa.

310
00:17:59,145 --> 00:18:00,446
You do?

311
00:18:00,479 --> 00:18:02,982
She can't contact you directly, so.

312
00:18:03,015 --> 00:18:05,651
I know, she doesn't have a cell.

313
00:18:06,586 --> 00:18:07,420
You know her well.

314
00:18:08,387 --> 00:18:12,658
She asked
if you'd like to dine with her.

315
00:18:13,359 --> 00:18:14,293
Dine?

316
00:18:15,595 --> 00:18:16,395
Okay.

317
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:19,899
Tell her I'm open next week.

318
00:18:20,466 --> 00:18:21,801
I will.

319
00:18:22,335 --> 00:18:23,336
Thank you.

320
00:18:26,739 --> 00:18:29,308
Something may be rekindled.

321
00:18:35,615 --> 00:18:39,318
So Ms. Jinko asked me
if I'd like to be her assistant.

322
00:18:40,987 --> 00:18:45,157
She really communicates with her team.

323
00:18:45,191 --> 00:18:47,526
She's so kind to me, too.

324
00:18:47,727 --> 00:18:49,528
I'd like to try it.

325
00:18:49,562 --> 00:18:52,098
So you're quitting? Nice knowing you.

326
00:18:52,131 --> 00:18:54,967
I'm not quitting,
it's just for a few days.

327
00:18:55,835 --> 00:18:59,005
Don't worry, I'll find someone new.

328
00:18:59,772 --> 00:19:01,841
I'm so kind too, aren't I?

329
00:19:11,217 --> 00:19:15,488
You're going to miss me when I'm gone.

330
00:19:17,523 --> 00:19:21,293
First, Ms. Jinko chooses the kimono.

331
00:19:21,327 --> 00:19:24,930
Then she creates the scene
as we shoot.

332
00:19:26,365 --> 00:19:28,434
Here's what we'll use this time.

333
00:19:28,968 --> 00:19:30,336
These three obi belts.

334
00:19:31,637 --> 00:19:34,073
They're by Sotatsu Nambu.

335
00:19:34,707 --> 00:19:38,477
Your job is to find accessories
and props to go with them

336
00:19:38,511 --> 00:19:40,446
by the day of the shoot.

337
00:19:41,380 --> 00:19:43,649
What I choose
might go in the magazine?

338
00:19:44,283 --> 00:19:45,117
It could.

339
00:19:45,317 --> 00:19:47,720
Wow, that's so crazy.

340
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:49,288
I'll do my best.

341
00:19:51,090 --> 00:19:53,826
You're lucky you have
such a great boss.

342
00:19:53,993 --> 00:19:55,895
Not like mine.

343
00:19:56,095 --> 00:19:58,197
Ms. Jinko really trusts you.

344
00:19:59,465 --> 00:20:00,399
I don't know.

345
00:20:00,433 --> 00:20:05,304
Sure, she asked for
your opinion first.

346
00:20:05,971 --> 00:20:08,774
I really can't tell though.

347
00:20:12,244 --> 00:20:15,815
I'm actually her 6th assistant.

348
00:20:16,615 --> 00:20:18,084
I could be fired any day.

349
00:20:18,417 --> 00:20:19,618
Really?

350
00:20:21,020 --> 00:20:26,792
But I really adore the works
Ms. Jinko creates.

351
00:20:27,827 --> 00:20:30,529
I want to work for her forever.

352
00:20:30,696 --> 00:20:32,198
And give it my best.

353
00:20:38,637 --> 00:20:41,674
Wait, stop, hey!

354
00:20:42,641 --> 00:20:43,542
You scared me.

355
00:20:44,310 --> 00:20:46,011
Oh, it's you.

356
00:20:46,278 --> 00:20:47,346
Thought you quit.

357
00:20:47,379 --> 00:20:50,616
I have not.
I just came to get some stuff.

358
00:20:51,951 --> 00:20:54,987
I have to do everything
now that you're away.

359
00:20:55,621 --> 00:20:56,555
Sorry.

360
00:21:02,261 --> 00:21:05,931
I guess we do need you,
useless as you are.

361
00:21:07,566 --> 00:21:08,701
Come back soon.

362
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:15,841
Ms. Suzuki.

363
00:21:16,275 --> 00:21:17,042
Can we talk?

364
00:21:19,311 --> 00:21:23,282
Remember that guy Oashi
from the mixer?

365
00:21:23,449 --> 00:21:25,351
Yeah, what about him?

366
00:21:25,384 --> 00:21:28,954
He called and asked me to go
on a glamping day trip.

367
00:21:29,388 --> 00:21:31,957
- A date?
- No, as a group.

368
00:21:33,025 --> 00:21:34,927
Will you come too? Please?

369
00:21:35,194 --> 00:21:36,295
Me? Really?

370
00:21:36,328 --> 00:21:38,430
You seem like the glamping type.

371
00:21:38,798 --> 00:21:41,200
I wouldn't say that I am.

372
00:21:41,233 --> 00:21:42,902
But yeah, sure.

373
00:21:43,102 --> 00:21:46,205
Really? Thanks.

374
00:21:46,839 --> 00:21:51,343
Why don't we invite one more person?
Someone from the editing department.

375
00:21:51,377 --> 00:21:53,045
Sure, I guess.

376
00:21:53,078 --> 00:21:57,583
There's only one guy now,
so maybe we should invite another.

377
00:21:58,150 --> 00:22:02,521
But not Mr. Handa. That'd be weird.
What do you think?

378
00:22:11,830 --> 00:22:14,900
How about maybe Mr. Nakazawa?

379
00:22:15,134 --> 00:22:16,435
Mr. Nakazawa?

380
00:22:18,270 --> 00:22:22,074
You're right, he's a guy
and he's in the editing department.

381
00:22:23,075 --> 00:22:26,212
Sure, if there's nobody else.

382
00:22:26,912 --> 00:22:29,014
Talk to him then, will you?

383
00:22:43,262 --> 00:22:44,296
Good morning.

384
00:22:44,496 --> 00:22:45,564
Good morning.

385
00:22:46,532 --> 00:22:48,133
Didn't think you'd come.

386
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:50,302
You asked me to.

387
00:22:51,470 --> 00:22:52,771
Is this it?

388
00:22:52,805 --> 00:22:55,641
Mr. Oashi should be here soon too.

389
00:22:56,742 --> 00:22:57,643
Hey!

390
00:22:59,311 --> 00:23:00,279
Why?

391
00:23:01,180 --> 00:23:02,581
Nami!

392
00:23:03,515 --> 00:23:04,817
Why is he here?

393
00:23:05,117 --> 00:23:07,920
Oashi isn't feeling well, so I came.

394
00:23:07,953 --> 00:23:09,989
I'm sorry.

395
00:23:10,022 --> 00:23:12,091
My stomach hurts.

396
00:23:12,124 --> 00:23:13,392
He asked me to take his place.

397
00:23:14,426 --> 00:23:15,894
You were at that mixer.

398
00:23:15,928 --> 00:23:17,263
Oh yeah.

399
00:23:18,330 --> 00:23:20,666
So we all know each other.

400
00:23:21,367 --> 00:23:22,968
Mean senpai is here too.

401
00:23:23,102 --> 00:23:24,603
Not in front of him.

402
00:23:24,970 --> 00:23:25,738
Oops.

403
00:23:27,106 --> 00:23:27,940
Hi.

404
00:23:28,307 --> 00:23:29,708
Come on, let's go.

405
00:23:36,248 --> 00:23:37,716
Oh no.

406
00:23:38,717 --> 00:23:42,321
The food for the barbecue
wasn't in the option.

407
00:23:42,354 --> 00:23:44,890
What should we do now?

408
00:23:45,291 --> 00:23:48,527
Could you go buy some food
with Mr. Junnosuke?

409
00:23:49,828 --> 00:23:54,333
Here's a list for
a perfect barbecue for four.

410
00:23:54,366 --> 00:23:55,434
I'll send you the link.

411
00:23:55,467 --> 00:23:56,535
I'll go too.

412
00:23:59,405 --> 00:24:01,840
No, you help Ms. Haruka.

413
00:24:01,874 --> 00:24:03,809
You'll need help, right?

414
00:24:06,145 --> 00:24:06,945
Fine.

415
00:24:07,846 --> 00:24:08,847
Let's go, Nami.

416
00:24:08,881 --> 00:24:10,482
See you later.

417
00:24:10,516 --> 00:24:12,217
Can we buy marshmallows?

418
00:24:12,251 --> 00:24:13,552
Let's toast them.

419
00:24:14,186 --> 00:24:15,454
Sure, why not.

420
00:24:20,059 --> 00:24:20,826
Let's go.

421
00:24:24,029 --> 00:24:27,633
I wonder what that kiss
on the forehead was about.

422
00:24:28,567 --> 00:24:33,439
And how he said he was my boyfriend.

423
00:24:36,141 --> 00:24:38,043
How about sashimi?

424
00:24:38,310 --> 00:24:40,913
I don't think that's barbecue-like.

425
00:24:41,547 --> 00:24:45,484
Is he just a simple guy?

426
00:24:46,919 --> 00:24:49,988
I just saw something on my phone.

427
00:24:50,022 --> 00:24:53,492
There's a place nearby
where you can see tons of stars.

428
00:24:53,525 --> 00:24:54,960
Let's go see them, you and me.

429
00:24:55,427 --> 00:24:56,595
What about the others?

430
00:24:57,196 --> 00:24:59,498
I think they'll want to be alone too.

431
00:24:59,865 --> 00:25:03,569
That career woman girl
kept glancing at mean senpai.

432
00:25:04,303 --> 00:25:06,905
So you're intuitive
when it comes to others.

433
00:25:08,841 --> 00:25:13,379
Wait, he just said
they'll want to be alone "too."

434
00:25:13,746 --> 00:25:15,247
"Too"?

435
00:25:16,782 --> 00:25:18,550
So let's go.

436
00:25:19,718 --> 00:25:21,520
He wants to be alone with me?

437
00:25:25,524 --> 00:25:26,425
This is good.

438
00:25:26,458 --> 00:25:28,293
Great.

439
00:25:28,527 --> 00:25:32,231
I made some basil sauce. Have some.

440
00:25:32,831 --> 00:25:35,033
I didn't know you cooked.

441
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:36,001
Why?

442
00:25:36,034 --> 00:25:38,771
You didn't seem like the type.

443
00:25:39,171 --> 00:25:40,672
- Really?
- Yeah.

444
00:25:41,507 --> 00:25:44,710
You seemed more like
the career woman type.

445
00:25:44,743 --> 00:25:45,811
I know.

446
00:25:45,978 --> 00:25:47,980
Of course I cook.

447
00:25:48,480 --> 00:25:50,315
Is it so weird that I cook?

448
00:25:50,616 --> 00:25:51,517
Maybe.

449
00:25:51,950 --> 00:25:54,052
What about you, Suzuki? You cook?

450
00:25:54,086 --> 00:25:55,521
Sure.

451
00:25:55,554 --> 00:25:58,690
Nothing fancy with basil and stuff.

452
00:25:58,724 --> 00:25:59,792
Cook something for me.

453
00:26:01,427 --> 00:26:02,594
Here you go.

454
00:26:02,628 --> 00:26:05,931
- You just grilled it.
- Why not?

455
00:26:05,964 --> 00:26:06,999
Like basil sauce stuff.

456
00:26:07,032 --> 00:26:08,634
How about this one?

457
00:26:08,667 --> 00:26:10,436
That's raw.

458
00:26:10,469 --> 00:26:11,303
Suzuki.

459
00:26:11,570 --> 00:26:14,473
So how's it like
working for Jinko Uekusa?

460
00:26:15,574 --> 00:26:18,644
She's such a great boss.

461
00:26:19,011 --> 00:26:22,314
She lets me try creative stuff.

462
00:26:22,347 --> 00:26:24,283
And listens to her team.

463
00:26:24,650 --> 00:26:27,352
She really makes
a great working environment.

464
00:26:28,220 --> 00:26:31,190
Some lucky people
get great bosses like that.

465
00:26:31,590 --> 00:26:33,392
Not us though.

466
00:26:34,393 --> 00:26:35,661
You think so?

467
00:26:35,694 --> 00:26:37,496
Definitely.

468
00:26:37,529 --> 00:26:40,532
But you know the sweets
for Dolly Harris?

469
00:26:40,566 --> 00:26:46,238
She told Mr. Handa to buy the sweet
potato bars for them from now on.

470
00:26:46,271 --> 00:26:47,406
Ms. Horai did?

471
00:26:47,439 --> 00:26:49,541
She met with the person in charge.

472
00:26:51,810 --> 00:26:54,913
Yeah, he loves Japanese sweets.
That's why I...

473
00:27:03,589 --> 00:27:05,157
Can I try your basil sauce?

474
00:27:05,524 --> 00:27:06,959
Sure, go ahead.

475
00:27:11,697 --> 00:27:12,731
I'll help.

476
00:27:12,965 --> 00:27:13,966
Oh, Nami.

477
00:27:16,468 --> 00:27:17,769
I'll do these.

478
00:27:23,842 --> 00:27:25,244
That's closer than one meter.

479
00:27:27,145 --> 00:27:28,780
You said it.

480
00:27:28,814 --> 00:27:31,116
To stay one meter away from you.

481
00:27:31,717 --> 00:27:32,484
Stand back!

482
00:27:33,318 --> 00:27:36,588
Keep a one-meter radius away from me.

483
00:27:37,189 --> 00:27:39,658
You're really doing that?

484
00:27:40,058 --> 00:27:40,959
Of course.

485
00:27:50,269 --> 00:27:51,169
Come to think of it...

486
00:27:52,037 --> 00:27:55,107
You've been keeping your distance
the whole day.

487
00:27:56,141 --> 00:27:57,376
Is it that funny?

488
00:28:10,422 --> 00:28:14,126
Maybe I'm overthinking things.

489
00:28:14,826 --> 00:28:15,594
About what?

490
00:28:21,066 --> 00:28:22,100
The stars.

491
00:28:23,802 --> 00:28:25,370
Let's go see them tonight.

492
00:28:27,806 --> 00:28:28,607
Really?

493
00:28:30,409 --> 00:28:31,176
All right!

494
00:28:33,712 --> 00:28:37,082
I've already checked to make sure
the bridge was firm enough.

495
00:28:37,115 --> 00:28:40,519
I can trust him, can't I?

496
00:28:47,326 --> 00:28:49,561
It's not that heavy.

497
00:28:51,363 --> 00:28:53,832
Ms. Suzuki, your phone's ringing.

498
00:28:54,199 --> 00:28:54,967
Coming.

499
00:28:55,567 --> 00:28:57,502
Do you know where Ms. Jinko is today?

500
00:28:57,936 --> 00:28:59,938
She's dining with an acquaintance.

501
00:29:00,672 --> 00:29:01,440
Something wrong?

502
00:29:01,707 --> 00:29:02,608
Do you know where?

503
00:29:03,108 --> 00:29:05,611
We're missing an obi belt
that we need tomorrow.

504
00:29:06,311 --> 00:29:08,914
I'll send you the address.
I'll go too.

505
00:29:11,316 --> 00:29:13,085
I'm sorry, I have to go back.

506
00:29:14,019 --> 00:29:17,789
It was a daytrip anyways.
I guess we should all go now.

507
00:30:13,211 --> 00:30:13,979
I'm sorry.

508
00:30:14,279 --> 00:30:16,648
I'm sorry, you were off work today
weren't you?

509
00:30:16,682 --> 00:30:17,549
It's fine.

510
00:30:17,582 --> 00:30:20,786
For some reason,
one of the obi belts didn't come.

511
00:30:20,819 --> 00:30:21,853
What will you do?

512
00:30:21,887 --> 00:30:24,356
It's impossible to rent another.

513
00:30:24,389 --> 00:30:28,293
Ms. Jinko will have to
think of a new layout tonight.

514
00:30:28,660 --> 00:30:31,396
We might make it in time
for tomorrow's shoot.

515
00:30:35,534 --> 00:30:36,301
Um...

516
00:30:38,203 --> 00:30:40,272
This dinner she's having tonight...

517
00:30:41,606 --> 00:30:45,377
You really haven't
changed a bit, Jinko.

518
00:30:47,112 --> 00:30:48,213
How are things?

519
00:30:49,047 --> 00:30:50,182
Not bad.

520
00:30:50,215 --> 00:30:51,917
But who knows about tomorrow?

521
00:30:53,885 --> 00:30:55,487
Any girlfriends?

522
00:30:55,987 --> 00:30:58,690
Like maybe Reiko?

523
00:31:01,493 --> 00:31:03,361
She has a right to choose too.

524
00:31:04,329 --> 00:31:07,399
She won't be interested
in such an old man.

525
00:31:09,634 --> 00:31:11,269
I wouldn't be too sure.

526
00:31:28,653 --> 00:31:31,957
Ten years ago

527
00:31:52,043 --> 00:31:53,411
We're missing one?

528
00:31:54,346 --> 00:31:55,547
What do you mean?

529
00:31:56,414 --> 00:31:57,315
Well...

530
00:31:58,416 --> 00:32:00,585
It didn't arrive on time.

531
00:32:00,952 --> 00:32:05,557
I've prepared a different obi belt
for today's shoot.

532
00:32:07,859 --> 00:32:11,563
I chose an obi by Sotatsu Nambu.

533
00:32:12,597 --> 00:32:14,933
This is like a dish cloth
compared to it.

534
00:32:15,934 --> 00:32:19,938
I chose this out of all the ones
available to us now.

535
00:32:20,238 --> 00:32:22,140
Why didn't you report this to me?

536
00:32:22,407 --> 00:32:25,043
You could've told me
instead of looking for that.

537
00:32:26,244 --> 00:32:27,679
Forgive me.

538
00:32:29,815 --> 00:32:34,486
I'm not angry about
the Sotatsu obi not arriving.

539
00:32:34,519 --> 00:32:38,089
I'm angry that you made a decision
without consulting me.

540
00:32:39,658 --> 00:32:42,327
I chose this obi because...

541
00:32:43,562 --> 00:32:45,197
The setup you created in...

542
00:32:45,230 --> 00:32:47,032
I'm done. I can't do this.

543
00:32:47,065 --> 00:32:48,200
You're fired.

544
00:32:50,969 --> 00:32:54,039
Wait, won't you listen to her please?

545
00:32:54,339 --> 00:32:58,476
Ms. Marika didn't want to bother
your dinner.

546
00:32:58,510 --> 00:33:02,214
And this obi was because
she knew your style and...

547
00:33:02,247 --> 00:33:04,049
You must have misunderstood.

548
00:33:04,883 --> 00:33:07,018
I don't need an assistant's opinion.

549
00:33:07,485 --> 00:33:11,089
She is not Jinko Uekusa.
Jinko Uekusa is I.

550
00:33:13,491 --> 00:33:14,860
My boss...

551
00:33:15,827 --> 00:33:20,265
When I said sweet potato bars
would be better, she accepted it.

552
00:33:22,767 --> 00:33:25,337
Obi belts are not sweet potato bars.

553
00:33:25,370 --> 00:33:28,340
Has Reiko taught you nothing?

554
00:33:29,274 --> 00:33:31,910
She's not a good teacher, is she?

555
00:33:32,210 --> 00:33:36,715
She may be a good businesswoman,
but an awful editor-in-chief.

556
00:33:39,651 --> 00:33:40,752
Ms. Horai is...

557
00:33:42,787 --> 00:33:45,023
My boss is not awful!

558
00:33:46,491 --> 00:33:48,894
Sure, she's pushy.

559
00:33:49,294 --> 00:33:52,264
She won't let me ride a cab
and makes me do kendama.

560
00:33:52,297 --> 00:33:54,633
And says her pleas
are worth 5 million yen.

561
00:33:54,666 --> 00:33:56,468
But sometimes...

562
00:33:57,035 --> 00:33:58,970
Just once in a while...

563
00:33:59,838 --> 00:34:02,540
She'll listen to
her assistant's opinion.

564
00:34:11,216 --> 00:34:12,217
Nice obi.

565
00:34:12,817 --> 00:34:13,585
Ms. Horai.

566
00:34:16,855 --> 00:34:20,225
I'm sorry for the trouble
my attendant caused you.

567
00:34:20,692 --> 00:34:24,195
I will not hinder you any further.

568
00:34:25,697 --> 00:34:29,601
We will do the rest of the shoot.

569
00:34:32,704 --> 00:34:34,673
Can I have some colored overlays?

570
00:34:51,589 --> 00:34:52,424
Okay.

571
00:34:59,164 --> 00:35:00,198
Shine light on the obi.

572
00:35:10,809 --> 00:35:11,743
This...

573
00:35:13,478 --> 00:35:13,645
Shine light on the obi.

574
00:35:13,645 --> 00:35:16,181
Ten years ago

575
00:35:34,599 --> 00:35:35,867
Reiko.

576
00:35:36,968 --> 00:35:37,769
Yes.

577
00:35:38,336 --> 00:35:40,038
Nowadays,

578
00:35:40,071 --> 00:35:44,643
your works are gorgeous
and dazzling.

579
00:35:45,243 --> 00:35:49,948
But I remember you
as a creative and bold artist.

580
00:35:50,849 --> 00:35:53,284
You transformed a simple obi

581
00:35:53,852 --> 00:35:57,455
into a dramatic piece of art.

582
00:35:58,256 --> 00:36:01,693
I remember the dazzling piece you made
as if it were yesterday.

583
00:36:03,962 --> 00:36:04,796
Marika.

584
00:36:09,434 --> 00:36:13,672
Did you see my old works too?

585
00:36:14,139 --> 00:36:15,306
Is that why?

586
00:36:16,808 --> 00:36:17,776
I...

587
00:36:19,444 --> 00:36:23,982
I joined the fashion industry
because I fell in love with that piece.

588
00:36:27,986 --> 00:36:28,820
I see.

589
00:36:32,991 --> 00:36:37,796
When I first started, nobody would
lend me expensive kimonos.

590
00:36:38,863 --> 00:36:39,931
But not now.

591
00:36:40,899 --> 00:36:46,571
I can choose whatever I want
and have a team to support me.

592
00:36:47,172 --> 00:36:48,339
But...

593
00:36:50,175 --> 00:36:51,743
I can't fail anymore.

594
00:36:53,344 --> 00:36:55,814
I must continue to be a top creator.

595
00:36:58,650 --> 00:37:01,453
So I stopped listening
to others' opinions.

596
00:37:05,123 --> 00:37:06,958
How fake I'd become.

597
00:37:13,064 --> 00:37:17,702
I consider you to be
my number one assistant.

598
00:37:23,041 --> 00:37:24,743
Forgive me for what I said.

599
00:37:27,112 --> 00:37:28,546
Thank you.

600
00:37:32,584 --> 00:37:35,286
I'll finish the shoot now.

601
00:37:39,557 --> 00:37:41,793
Let's redo this. Take off the obi.

602
00:37:42,393 --> 00:37:43,194
Please.

603
00:38:03,281 --> 00:38:04,883
Thank you for everything.

604
00:38:05,316 --> 00:38:09,721
You reminded me
of something important.

605
00:38:09,754 --> 00:38:10,955
So thank you.

606
00:38:12,190 --> 00:38:14,659
I'll give you your assistant back.

607
00:38:14,959 --> 00:38:16,494
You found a good one.

608
00:38:18,229 --> 00:38:22,033
You may take her with you to Paris
if you'd like.

609
00:38:22,066 --> 00:38:24,035
No, no thank you.

610
00:38:30,441 --> 00:38:33,545
I'm going to remarry.

611
00:38:34,078 --> 00:38:38,650
I was able to tell Ugaji too.

612
00:38:38,683 --> 00:38:40,051
He was happy for me.

613
00:38:42,587 --> 00:38:43,521
Congratulations.

614
00:38:50,795 --> 00:38:52,597
Look after him for me.

615
00:38:56,234 --> 00:39:00,104
You may be a top editor, but you're
a novice in the game of love.

616
00:39:02,707 --> 00:39:04,342
He's my ex-husband.

617
00:39:05,009 --> 00:39:07,212
I'm Horai. Nice to meet you.

618
00:39:07,879 --> 00:39:08,713
Hello.

619
00:39:11,583 --> 00:39:12,350
Um.

620
00:39:14,185 --> 00:39:15,620
You still have the tag on.

621
00:39:19,724 --> 00:39:20,825
Good luck.

622
00:39:22,427 --> 00:39:23,361
Bye.

623
00:39:45,617 --> 00:39:47,619
I'm back in the office, Ms. Horai.

624
00:39:49,639 --> 00:39:51,307
I thought you'd quit.

625
00:39:51,340 --> 00:39:52,909
Come on.

626
00:39:53,175 --> 00:39:55,278
I bet you missed me.

627
00:39:55,945 --> 00:39:59,882
I'm going to try to become
your number one assistant too...

628
00:40:02,118 --> 00:40:03,119
Hey!

629
00:40:03,986 --> 00:40:06,188
Wait for me!

630
00:40:07,256 --> 00:40:09,292
Look, I bought this.

631
00:40:09,492 --> 00:40:12,094
I'm going to work on
my sense of fashion.

632
00:40:13,796 --> 00:40:15,197
You still have the tag on.

633
00:40:20,336 --> 00:40:21,771
How embarrassing!

634
00:40:29,712 --> 00:40:32,315
I'm so nervous about tonight.

635
00:40:35,918 --> 00:40:38,487
Oh yeah, I deleted Junnosuke's number.

636
00:40:41,324 --> 00:40:42,825
I know.

637
00:40:43,292 --> 00:40:47,263
Nami? Sorry, but I'm not working
with Mr. Jun today.

638
00:40:47,296 --> 00:40:48,831
Oh, I see.

639
00:40:49,265 --> 00:40:52,868
Could you give me his number then?

640
00:40:52,902 --> 00:40:54,270
Yeah, sure.

641
00:40:54,637 --> 00:40:57,840
Hey, sorry I couldn't go
the other day.

642
00:40:57,873 --> 00:41:00,276
Did Haruka say anything about me?

643
00:41:00,309 --> 00:41:01,110
No.

644
00:41:03,279 --> 00:41:06,882
You think Mr. Jun and Haruka
might be getting close?

645
00:41:06,916 --> 00:41:09,418
And maybe fall in love?

646
00:41:09,452 --> 00:41:10,686
No, I don't think so.

647
00:41:10,720 --> 00:41:14,824
You're right.
Haruka isn't Mr. Jun's type.

648
00:41:15,224 --> 00:41:17,460
Oh really?

649
00:41:17,493 --> 00:41:19,895
Mr. Jun is a really determined lover.

650
00:41:19,929 --> 00:41:23,466
He's been in love with a pretty
childhood friend for years.

651
00:41:25,801 --> 00:41:28,971
She's not in Japan right now.

652
00:41:29,905 --> 00:41:33,009
Anyways,
I'll text you his number later.

653
00:41:34,644 --> 00:41:36,946
Hello? Hello?

654
00:41:40,082 --> 00:41:42,718
So what about the culture feature?

655
00:41:43,019 --> 00:41:45,121
Tell them what you were telling me.

656
00:41:45,154 --> 00:41:46,422
The interview.

657
00:41:46,455 --> 00:41:48,157
Don't you have the papers?

658
00:41:48,190 --> 00:41:49,392
What papers?

659
00:41:49,425 --> 00:41:51,327
Suzuki, the papers.

660
00:41:51,961 --> 00:41:52,728
Hurry.

661
00:41:53,529 --> 00:41:54,664
Sorry.

662
00:41:56,432 --> 00:41:58,801
I'm sorry.

663
00:42:00,870 --> 00:42:05,441
We'll go with violinist Rio Hasumi
as planned.

664
00:42:06,242 --> 00:42:10,646
She's coming back to Japan,
so it'll be easy to schedule it.

665
00:42:11,447 --> 00:42:13,015
How pretty.

666
00:42:17,686 --> 00:42:20,656
Here's Mr. Jun's number
Oashi

667
00:42:21,891 --> 00:42:25,061
He's already in love
with someone else.

668
00:42:35,271 --> 00:42:36,639
Why the long face?

669
00:42:37,173 --> 00:42:38,974
Nothing.

670
00:42:43,546 --> 00:42:45,948
It's raining, huh.

671
00:42:50,052 --> 00:42:52,388
Going to see the stars?

672
00:43:18,981 --> 00:43:22,785
I'll wait for you at the usual bench
at 5 PM.

673
00:43:48,410 --> 00:43:51,514
The stars. Let's go see them tonight.

674
00:43:52,181 --> 00:43:53,549
All right!

675
00:44:01,991 --> 00:44:07,096
I felt you'd really do your best
to help me out.

676
00:44:08,364 --> 00:44:10,099
That I could believe in you.

677
00:44:13,903 --> 00:44:17,373
That's why I chose you.

678
00:44:52,408 --> 00:44:54,376
Of course not.

679
00:45:28,911 --> 00:45:30,246
Junnosuke?

680
00:45:36,085 --> 00:45:37,086
Nami!

681
00:45:41,223 --> 00:45:42,725
I called you.

682
00:45:44,059 --> 00:45:46,028
I forgot my phone at the studio.

683
00:45:55,237 --> 00:45:56,705
Thanks for coming.

684
00:46:02,811 --> 00:46:05,814
It's raining.
We can't see the stars tonight.

685
00:46:36,245 --> 00:46:38,414
Please leave a message.

686
00:46:39,548 --> 00:46:42,484
Hi Jun. It's Rio.

687
00:46:43,886 --> 00:46:46,488
I just got back.

688
00:47:15,784 --> 00:47:15,985
Are we dating or not?

689
00:47:15,985 --> 00:47:17,486
Next episode

690
00:47:17,486 --> 00:47:19,121
You think you can do both?

691
00:47:19,388 --> 00:47:21,423
I want to do the house journal!

692
00:47:21,457 --> 00:47:24,159
No matter the result,
you'll move on to the next stage.

693
00:47:24,460 --> 00:47:27,396
The girl Junnosuke's
been in love with...

694
00:47:27,663 --> 00:47:28,630
It's important.

695
00:47:28,864 --> 00:47:30,566
I need you to say it.
